    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1045"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1045">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor for the <gloss type="from">Department of
                            State</gloss> to the German Ambassador</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BCJHV1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bernstorff</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of state</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-23">
                        <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: In reply to your note of the
                    21st instant, with reference to the British <persName>S. S. <hi rend="italic"
                            >Mallina</hi>
                    </persName> and <persName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Tremeadow</hi>
                    </persName>, which you state have served as tenders to British cruisers, and are
                    demanding coal in the Panama Canal Zone, I would advise you that these vessels
                    have been considered by the Canal authorities as coming under rule 2 of the
                    President’s proclamation of November 13 last in relation to the neutrality of
                    the Panama Canal Zone,<note n="2" xml:id="d1045fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_552">p. 552</ref>.</note>
                    which <pb facs="0968" n="654" xml:id="pg_654"/> accords to transports or fleet
                    auxiliaries the same treatment as that given to belligerent vessels of war.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
